<H3> <TI>   `Great Importance' Seen in Damascus Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601055394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 6 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0601055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Well-informed Israeli sources attribute great 
importance to a statement made by a Radio Damascus commentator 
that in exchange for a withdrawal from all the occupied 
territories, Israel will reap the fruits of peace on all fronts, 
without exception. Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz 
reports that according to these sources, this is the first 
statement of its kind. They believe it was made in anticipation 
of the Clinton-al-Asad summit. 

</TEXT>

