<F P=102>  TA0601102294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 6 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0601102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldier was stabbed 
at the French Hill junction in north Jerusalem a short time ago. 
The assailant was shot and killed by Border Police soldiers. 
Our correspondent 'Ofra Nehmad reports that the wounded 
soldier, who was taken to Hadassah-'En Kerem Hospital, is listed 
in moderate condition. 
  Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that the terrorist 
jumped the soldier, stabbed him several times, grabbed his 
personal weapon, and fled the site. Border Police soldiers 
pursued him in a jeep and shot and killed him. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0900 GMT on 6 January 
reports that "an Arab youth was wounded by IDF gunfire in the 
Jabalyah refugee camp this morning. Our correspondent Moti Amir 
reports the youth threw a burning tire at an IDF outpost. The 
soldiers manning the outpost, who suspected that a bomb was 
planted in the tire, shot the youth and wounded him in the leg. 
The youth was evacuated to a Gaza hospital for treatment."] 

</TEXT>

