<H3> <TI>   IDF To Pave Road With Jordan Bypassing Jericho </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0501180294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 5 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0501180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has recently begun 
to expand the border road with Jordan prior to the paving of a 
temporary road which bypasses Jericho. David Levi, head of the 
Jordan Rift Valley Regional Council, said that the bypass road 
would be built east of Almog junction near Bet Ha'arava up to 
the settlement of Na'ama. Our settlement affairs correspondent 
Gil Litman has learned that a permanent road closer to Jericho 
will be built later. The length of the permanent road will be 
17 km. It will have two bridges and will cost 40 million 
shekels. 

</TEXT>

