<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Receives Lebanon's al-Hariri </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0501152794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1215 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0501152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi received Lebanese 
Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri at 1000 today. Their discussions 
dealt with the relations of brotherhood, cooperation, and 
coordination between the two fraternal countries and ways of 
promoting them in all fields in the service and the interest of 
the two fraternal countries and peoples. 
  An official session of talks began at 1100 today between the 
Syrian side under Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi and the 
Lebanese side under Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri. Dr. Salim 
Yasin, deputy prime minister for Economic Affairs; Engineer 
'Abd-al-Rahman Madani, minister of Irrigation; Engineer Kamil 
al-Baba, minister of Electricity; Nasir Qaddur, minister of 
state for Foreign Affairs; Dr. Nadir al-Nabulsi, minister of Oil 
and Mineral Resources; and directors and advisers attended the 
session on the Syrian side. On the Lebanese side, it was 
attended by Ilyas Hubayqah, minister of Water and Electricity, 
and Marun Asmar, chairman of the Lebanese Electricity 
Corporation. 
  The two sides discussed economic cooperation between the two 
countries and the joint ventures that are being studied, 
particularly in the field of power generation. The two sides 
also discussed the scopes of joint cooperation in all fields, in 
light of priorities and needs, to enhance the bonds of 
brotherhood, cooperation, and coordination between the two 
countries and to attain the two fraternal people's interests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

