<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's Qaddumi Arrives for Coordination Meetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   King Confers With Qaddumi, Delegation </H4>
<F P=102> JN0501200894 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1900 GMT 5 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0501200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn received at the Royal 
Hashemite Court this evening Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO 
Political Department, and the delegation accompanying him. 
During the meeting, they exchanged views on latest developments 
in the peace process and the importance of true and serious 
coordination between the Jordanian and Palestinian sides in 
light of the bases of His Majesty King Husayn's two recent 
speeches and in light of objective bases that will serve and 
secure the interests of the two fraternal peoples. 
  For his part, Faruq Qaddumi stressed the importance of 
Jordan's constructive role in defending the Palestine question, 
as well as the services this country extended to the Palestinian 
people and their just cause. He said that the PLO admits the 
courageous Jordanian role in defending the rights of the 
Palestinian people and extending services to them in various 
areas. He also referred to Jordan's role in absorbing 
Palestinian immigrants despite its limited material potential. 
The meeting was attended on the Jordanian side by Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, Royal Hashemite Court 
Chief His Excellency al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, Deputy Prime 
Minister Sa'id al-Tall, and Information Minister Jawad 
al-'Anani. It was attended on the Palestinian side by Muhammad 
Zuhdi al-Nashashibi, Yasir 'Amr, and the Palestinian ambassador 
in Amman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

