<H3> <TI>   PLO's Qaddumi Arrives for Coordination Meetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meetings Resume 6 Jan </H4>
<F P=102> JN0601131794 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 6 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0601131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Jordanian and Palestinian sides resumed their 
meetings at the Foreign Ministry today. These meetings are a 
continuation of the two working sessions held yesterday. Dr. 
Sa'id al-Tall, the deputy prime minister and minister of higher 
education, headed the Jordanian side, while Faruq Qaddumi, head 
of the PLO Political Department, headed the Palestinian side. 
  The second session was held yesterday during which the two 
sides discussed bilateral relations, issues dealing with the 
peace process, and Jordanian-Palestinian coordination on these 
issues. 

</TEXT>

