<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Canadian Official Received by Al-Majali </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0501125694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 5 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0501125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali today 
received in his office at the Prime Ministry Bob Rae, the 
premier of the Canadian province of Ontario, and his 
accompanying delegation. During the meeting, the two sides 
discussed bilateral relations and the need to reinforce, 
promote, and develop these relations in all spheres. They also 
discussed ways to reinforce economic relations as well as the 
peace process, the stages it reached, and the obstacles it is 
facing, especially on the Jordanian track, such as the refugee 
problem, waters, and evacuees. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Dr. Ma'n Abu-Nuwar also attended the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

