<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Postal, Telecommunications Pact Signed With Turkmenistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501201594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran and the Republic of 
Turkmenistan signed their first postal and telecommunications 
agreement in Tehran. 
  According to the said agreement, a 480-channel telephone 
exchange, linking Tehran to Ashgabat, will be inaugurated 
tomorrow. The telephone link will provide direct telephone 
contacts between Iran and Turkmenistan. In addition, through 
that service the peoples of other Central Asian countries will 
also be able to have telecommunications contact with the Islamic 
Republic of Iran and the rest of the world. 
  Other points in the said protocol include establishment of 
regular postal services. The air services organization of the 
Ministry of Post, Telegraph &amp; Telephone will handle letter 
and 
parcel mail between Tehran and Ashkabad. Yesterday the Turkmen 
communications minister inaugurated the first flight of the said 
postal service at Payam airport. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

