<H3> <TI>   Tamil Nadu Chief Minister Made Chancellor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0501162694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0501162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Tamil Nadu Assembly has passed two bills making 
the chief minister chancellor of all the 13 universities in the 
state in place of the governor. Replying to the debate, the 
education minister, Mr. K. Ponnuswamy, allayed fears there would 
be interference in the day-to-day functioning of the 
universities. He claimed that it is well within the legislative 
competence and jurisdiction of the house to make the chief 
minister chancellor of the universities. 
  The Congress-I, the Janata Party, the CPI [Communist Party 
of 
India], the CPI-M [Communist Party of India-Marxist] and the MGR 
Anna DMK [M.G. Ramachandran Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam] 
parties have criticized the Tamil Nadu Government for violating 
federal principles and showing disrespect to the governor by 
bringing forward the bills. They expressed the view the bills 
would pave the way for encroachment in the day-to-day 
functioning of the universities. 

</TEXT>

