<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar, Dostam Demand Rabbani's Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601065194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 6 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601065194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A representative of Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami in 
Islamabad announced that General Dostam and Golboddin Hekmatyar 
have given President Borhanoddin Rabbani 48 hours to resign. 
  According to the Central News Unit from Islamabad, the 
statement by the opposition groups asked the political groups in 
Afghanistan to meet to decide on a replacement for Borhanoddin 
Rabbani and to implement an immediate cease-fire. 
  Kabul and some other cities in Afghanistan have been the 
venue of intense internecine fighting in the past few days. 

</TEXT>

