<H3> <TI>   Iranian Embassy Tries to Broker Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601114994 Tehran IRNA in English 1538 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kabul, Jan. 5, IRNA -- Iranian Embassy in Kabul has 
launched serious efforts to broker a cease-fire among the Afghan 
rival factions, Iran's ambassador to Kabul, Gholamreza Haddadi, 
told reporters here Wednesday. 
  Haddadi stated that as far as negotiations with different 
Afghan rival factions are concerned, they seem to be ready to 
accept mediation for establishment of a cease-fire. 
  "Afghan rival factions believe that none of the country's 
political parties should be excluded from the future government 
of Afghanistan," Haddadi added. 

</TEXT>

