<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar Would Welcome Pakistan as Mediator </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0501155594 Hong Kong AFP in English 1541 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0501155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, Jan 5 (AFP) -- Afghan Prime Minister 
Golboddin Hekmatyar would welcome any visit from Pakistan aimed 
at restoring peace in Kabul, his official representative here 
said Wednesday. 
  "Hekmatyar has always welcomed visitors from Pakistan," 
Mangal Hoseyn said in a statement on the Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic 
Party of Afghanistan] leader's response to a planned mediation 
trip to Kabul by Pakistani Foreign Minister Asif Ahmad Ali. 
  The foreign minister had to put off a scheduled visit after 
fighting broke out in Kabul on New Year's Day. 
  "We respect Pakistan's concern for peace and stability in 
Afghanistan and are always ready to receive any delegation from 
the brotherly country," Hoseyn said. 

