<F P=102>  TA0401160594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0401160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting between Palestinian representatives and 
British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd at Orient House in East 
Jerusalem ended a short while ago. Our correspondent Golan 
Yokhpaz filed the following report: 
  [Begin Yokhpaz recording] The meeting between the seven 
Palestinian representatives -- including the PLO ambassador to 
London -- and British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd ended 
without any declaration stating that progress has been made or 
that Hurd made some contribution to promoting the 
Israeli-Palestinian negotiations. Speaking beneath a PLO and a 
British flag, the British secretary said that the meeting was 
good and that in it, the parties discussed the future of the 
Israeli-Palestinian negotiations. 
  Speaking at the conclusion of the meeting, Dr. Hanan 
'Ashrawi 
said: Britain plays an important role in the negotiating 
relations between Israel and the PLO. Asked about progress in 
the negotiations, 'Ashrawi said: Well, goodwill alone is not 
sufficient for the continuation of the Israeli-PLO negotiations. 
We need very serious, concrete, and constructive action in 
order to make progress. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

