<H3> <TI>   Paper Reports `Strained' PLO-Iraqi Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0401124294 Amman AL-'AHD in Arabic 4 Jan 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0401124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-'AHD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- AL-'AHD -- A high-ranking Palestinian 
source in Amman has said that Iraqi-Palestinian relations are 
not in good shape because of Iraq's position on the peace 
process, which opposes the stance of the PLO. 
  It has been learned that these relations became strained 
recently after Saddam Husayn offered to let Palestinian troops 
in Iraq join Iraqi troops, something which angered Yasir 'Arafat 
and prompted him to delay the move of Palestinian troops from 
Iraq to Jericho. 

</TEXT>

