<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President on Independence, Foreign Hostility </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501142894 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 5 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lieutenant General Umar Hasan Ahmad al-Bashir, 
president of the republic, has described the celebrations of 
independence day as something that should continue and should be 
strengthened. 
  In his meeting this morning with the media leaders, he said 
that the revolution's serious work to implement the principles 
of independence was what instigated others to adopt a hostile 
attitude in their dealings with Sudan, a matter which instigated 
us to be even more committed to our independence. In this 
context he pointed out that opening al-Tahadi [defiance] road 
was a confirmation of independence. 
  Lieutenant General al-Bashir stressed the need for numerous 
similar great projects in order to get Sudan out of the state of 
inherited poverty. He stressed the importance of constructing 
al-Hamdab dam, which will provide 1.250 million mw of 
electricity in addition to irrigation water. [passage omitted] 

