<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman on Clinton Letter to Kashmiri Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0601145294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0601145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi says that it entirely shares the growing 
global interests on the strict observation of human rights. An 
External Affairs Ministry spokesman said that India is committed 
to strengthening the institutions relevant to the upholding of 
human rights in India. 
  Commenting on a reported letter from the U.S. President, Mr. 
Bill Clinton, to one Dr. Ghulam Ali Fai of New York, the 
spokesman said that India trusts that when Mr. Clinton referred 
to respect for human rights, it was in the context of gross 
violation of human rights by militants and terrorists, aided and 
abetted from outside India. 

</TEXT>

