Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hemi Shalev and Washington-based correspondent </F>
Avino'am Bar-Yosef] 
  [Excerpt] Sources in the prime minister's bureau yesterday 
confirmed that Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin is not enthusiastic 
about the idea of posting U.S. troops on the Golan Heights. 
  In a closed-door discussion held in the last few days Rabin 
also referred to the Palestinian desire for deploying U.S. 
forces at the border crossing points: "I do not want any 
American mother to cry on our account." Rabin adduced the 
example of U.S. intervention in Somalia, recalling the grave 
impact that the death of only a handful of American soldiers had 
on U.S. public opinion. [passage omitted] 

