<F P=101> Israel </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Plans Traffic Arteries To Link Jericho, Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3112115193 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 31 Dec 93 p 3--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> TA3112115193 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv MA'ARIV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alex Fishman] </F>
  [Text] Plans drafted by the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
General Staff and relayed in the form of recommendations to the 
Palestinians propose linking the two self-administration 
regions, Gaza and Jericho, with three traffic arteries. Free 
traffic between the two autonomous regions is a part of the Oslo 
document and the Cairo draft. 
  -- The northern artery: the Erez checkpoint, Ashqelon 
junction, Bene Deror junction, Bet Lid Junction, Tulkarm, 
Nabulus, al-Jiftliq, Jericho. 
  -- The central artery: the Erez checkpoint, Kefar Silver 
junction, Re'em junction, Hulda junction, Latrun junction, 
Giv'at Ze'ev, al-Jib, 'Anatot, Almog junction, Jericho. 
  -- The southern artery: the Erez checkpoint, Ashqelon 
junction, Pelugot junction, Bet Guvrin junction, Tarqumiyah, 
Hebron, Bethlehem, Abu-Dis, Almog junction, Jericho. 
  The Palestinians prefer to build a new axis that will 
connect 
the West Bank with Gaza and be controlled by the autonomous 
Palestinian authority. 

</TEXT>

