<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taba Negotiators To Discuss Israeli, PLO Drafts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601152394 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0601152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by political correspondent Udi Segal--recorded] </F>
  [Excerpts] Israel is suggesting that the Taba talks be 
held on a continuous basis. The talks will resume on 10 
January. Heads of both delegations, Dr. Nabil Sha'th and Major 
General Amnon Shahaq, will discuss the two drafts Israel and the 
PLO have formulated. Several of the disputed issues in the 
drafts are not at all simple: For example, control over travel 
axes in Gaza, the size and authority of the Palestinian council, 
the manner in which civilian authority will be transferred, and 
other issues. [passage omitted] 
  A senior political source said today that it is worth paying 
attention to the fact that the compromise formula makes no 
mention of the demands Yasir 'Arafat presented in the documents 
faxed to Israel over the last week. These demands deviated from 
the Cairo understandings and even from the Oslo document of 
principles. 

</TEXT>

