<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Talks End in Paris; Progress Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0701081894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 7 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0701081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Paris, Israel and Palestinian negotiators have 
ended the fifth round of economic talks, and progress has been 
reported. A Qol Yisra'el reporter says advances were made in the 
areas of agriculture and taxation; however, the Palestinians 
presented new requests in the area of banking. The Palestinians 
continue to demand their own currency and a central bank, and 
are opposed to Israeli representation at customs at border 
crossing points. The two sides say the talks are due to resume 
in 10 days. 

</TEXT>

