<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Meets Turkish Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601174694 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] National Defense Minister Abdelaziz Ben Dhia held 
talks this morning with his Turkish counterpart Mehmet Golhan, 
who started his official visit to Tunisia yesterday. During the 
meeting, the two ministers reviewed a number of issues of common 
interest, particularly those relating to bilateral relations. 
  After the talks, the two ministers attended the opening of 
the proceedings of the Joint Military Committee that will 
examine several aspects of Tunisian-Turkish cooperation in the 
military field. On this occasion, the two ministers highlighted 
the importance of this committee and stressed the understanding 
that always prevailed during its meetings. This, they said, 
allowed the development of bilateral cooperation in this field 
and opened new avenues. 

</TEXT>

