<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contacts Held for Arab `Reconciliation' Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0601142794 Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' in Arabic 6 Jan 94 pp 1, 
16 </F>

<F P=103> JN0601142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman--AKHBAR AL-USBU' has learned that extensive 
Jordanian-Gulf contacts are currently being held to pave the way 
for holding an Arab summit to produce Arab reconciliation 
committees to settle the existing political and border 
differences among several Arab states, and to draft a formula 
for a new Arab order that can coexist with the new world order 
and make gains for the Arab nation. 
  Jordanian Foreign Ministry sources stressed that these 
contacts have begun with the visits to Jordan by the foreign 
ministers of Qatar, Syria, Egypt, and Palestine. The sources 
said that these contacts will resume next week when the Omani 
foreign minister visits Jordan on Saturday [8 January]. 
  The Foreign Ministry sources said that these political Arab 
moves constitute a translation of the official and popular 
stands of Jordan, which feels that coordinating Arab stands and 
achieving Arab solidarity constitutes the first step toward the 
Arabs' entry into the modern age as an influential political and 
economic force. 
  The sources noted that Qatar and Oman are currently seeking 
to expand their political activities to hold a summit that will 
be the most important and prominent Arab summit, especially 
since it will put an end to fragmentation and estrangement and 
achieve Arab unity and solidarity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

