<H3> <TI>   Arab Interior Ministers' Meeting Concludes </TI></H3>
<H4>   Iraqi Minister Addresses Conference </H4>
<F P=102> JN0601183894 Baghdad INA in English 1350 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0601183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, Jan. 6 (INA)--Iraq's Justice Minister Shabib 
al-Maliki has affirmed that Iraq under leadership of President 
Saddam Husayn is ready to render all forms of support for the 
joint Arab action with the aim of countering enemies of the Arab 
nation and defending the destiny national causes. 
  Addressing the Arab Interior Ministers Council last night, 
Mr. al-Maliki said that the blockade imposed on Iraq since 
August 1990 did not prevent Iraq from performing its national 
role and adopt best means of cooperation with the brethren in 
different fields, chief among which the fields pertaining to 
consolidating stability and the pan-Arab security. 
  The minister also called for significance of the joint Arab 
action for the Arab human being and the Arab destiny and 
deepening the inter-Arab cooperation to confront with all forms 
of intervention and foreign ambitions. 

</TEXT>

