<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Majid Receives Message From al-Muntasir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601190594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid today received a written message from 'Umar 
al-Muntasir, Libyan secretary of the People's Bureau for Foreign 
Liaison and International Cooperation. The message deals with 
the latest developments in the Libyan-Western crisis in light of 
the UN embargo on Libya and Libya's contacts with the United 
Nations and international parties in this regard. The message 
expresses Libya's appreciation for the efforts being made by the 
Arab League secretary general and the need for continuing these 
efforts in the future. 

</TEXT>

