<H3> <TI>   Israeli Air Raid on PFLP-GC Position Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601174294 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 6 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the latest reports from the south, a 
Palestinian was wounded in the Israeli raid on a position 
belonging to the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] on the al-Na'imah hills this 
afternoon. However, Palestinian sources said that the wounded 
person is a Lebanese civilian who happened to be driving his car 
in the vicinity during the raid. He was wounded in the hand. 
  Our correspondent in al-Nabatiyah reports that the Iqlim 
al-Tuffah hills, particularly Mlita, 'Ayn Bu Siwar, and 
al-Luwayzah, came under intermittent bombardment from the 
Israeli positions in al-Zaffatah. The Israeli artillery 
emplacements on the hills of Sujud and al-Suwayda' raked 
opposite positions. Two Israeli helicopters overflew the hills 
facing the city of al-Nabatiyah. 

</TEXT>

