<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Leader: No Clashes With Interim Authority </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601152594 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 5 Jan 94 pp 1, 18 </F>
<F P=103> TA0601152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Gaza, QUDS PRESS -- A Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] leader has said that his movement will not participate 
in any authority, stemming from the Palestinian-Israeli 
Declaration of Principles, during the interim stage in the 
occupied territories. 
  Dr. Mahmud al-Zahhar stressed to QUDS PRESS: Naturally, we 
will not participate in any legislative or executive institution 
linked to self-rule so that we will not bear the responsibility 
for signing an agreement that is incompatible with our doctrine 
and political program. Hamas, however, will participate in any 
elections to choose the Palestinian people's representatives 
provided those elections are not connected to the agreement or 
to any preconditions that might divert the elections toward 
political goals that are inconsistent with our tendencies. 
  Al-Zahhar ruled out any clash between the Palestinian 
authority expected to be established in the occupied territories 
and Hamas. He said: We will endeavor to solve our problems on a 
personal level. In the event that any problem develops we will 
ask to meet with PLO officials or the authority to resolve the 
differences. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

