<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas: `Major Operations' Against Israel Vowed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0601201194 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 6 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> JN0601201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Amman, Muhammad Nazzal, Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] spokesman in Jordan, has voiced the movement's 
determination to carry out major operations in the occupied 
territories. In an interview with the French magazine V.S. DAY 
[name as heard] published today, Nazzal said that the coming 
days will witness successive and escalating operations. 
  Nazzal indicated that since the signing of the Oslo 
agreement 
between the PLO and Israel, the intifadah has acquired a new 
dimension represented by the use of automatic weapons and 
suicide operations. He stressed Hamas' refusal to cease-fire 
with the Israelis. He said that the movement is committed to 
continuing struggle against the Israeli occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

