<H3> <TI>   Rabin: Palestinians' Release `Goodwill Gesture' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0701081494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 7 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0701081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning 101 Palestinian prisoners were 
released from prison installations in southern Israel. They are 
now on their way home. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan reports 
that the prisoners, most of whom were released from Qezi'ot 
prison, are now being driven home by bus. 
  Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin decided to release the 
prisoners 
as a goodwill gesture prior to the resumption of the Taba talks. 
The prisoners belong to organizations that support the 
political process. None of them were convicted of either murder 
or manslaughter. 

</TEXT>

