<H3> <TI>   Increase in `Positive' Syrian Statements Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0701072694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 7 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0701072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Syrian Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam 
recently spoke in public about the possibility of Syria 
recognizing Israel and normalizing relations with it within the 
framework of the peace negotiations. These issues, Khaddam 
said, are part of the negotiations, and it is too early to 
decide on the format of relations. 
  Political sources in Jerusalem told our political 
correspondent Shlomo Raz that this is the first time that a 
senior Syrian statesman has spoken about normalization. The 
sources noted that prior to the meeting between Presidents 
Clinton and al-Asad, there has been an increase in positive 
statements coming from Damascus with regard to the peace process. 

</TEXT>

