<H3> <TI>   Israel To Take Part in Amman Economic Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601181394 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0601181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres has disclosed that 
Israel will participate in an international economic conference 
slated to be held in Amman in the spring. Representatives from 
regional states and from large U.S. and European economic 
organizations are to take part in this conference. He added 
that the conference's aim will to be mobilize capital in a bid 
to invest it in the region with the advent of the era of peace. 
  Mr. Peres said that Israel has begun preparing detailed 
programs relating to water desalinization and the construction 
of roads and harbors to be presented at the conference. 

</TEXT>

