<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF `Forcibly' Removes Protesting Settlers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601172694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 6 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0601172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A confrontation has developed in the last few 
minutes between settlers, who had blocked the Qalqilyah-Nabulus 
road near the Tzofim settlement, and IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
soldiers. Our correspondent Gil Litman reports that members of 
the security forces have started forcibly removing Tzofim 
settlers who are sitting in the road, blocking it to protest 
what they term the deteriorating state of security in the area. 
  Our correspondent adds that several settlers have been 
detained, and the IDF is now proceeding with an evacuation. A 
traffic jam has been created by the fracas. The IDF has 
declared the site a closed military zone. 

</TEXT>

