<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Settler-Army Skirmish Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0601201894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 6 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0601201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The confrontation between settlers and the security 
forces at the Tzofim junction on the Qalqilyah-Nabulus road 
ended a short while ago. Our correspondent Gil Litman reports 
that about 10 settlers were detained and some settlers were 
injured in the course of the confrontation. The head of the 
Samaria Local Council acted to soothe the flaring tempers. Army 
and police troops are still in the area, which was declared a 
closed military zone. The settlers were protesting the 
deteriorating state of security. 

</TEXT>

