<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabbani Spokesman: Current Battles `Holy War' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601172394 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] 'Aziz Morad, spokesman for the Afghan president, 
in an interview with the Central News Unit in Kabul spoke of 
current battles in Kabul as a holy war and a second revolution. 
He said: These battles will continue until there is total 
victory over the opposition. 
  He also announced an agreement on a temporary cease-fire to 
transfer the wounded. 
  The spokesman for Rabbani also spoke about heavy clashes in 
northern Afghanistan and around the city of Mazar-e-Sharif and 
denied the announcement of any cease-fire in that city. 
  'Aziz Morad said three areas in the Faryab Province, in 
northern Afghanistan, have come under the control of forces of 
General Esmai'l Khan, an important commander of Jami'at-e Eslami 
[Islamic Society of Afghanistan] in western Afghanistan. 
  Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan] and the 
Northern 
Meli-ye Eslami [Islamic Front] Movement say they have also 
achieved fresh victories in the battle fields in northern 
Afghanistan. 
  They announced the main condition for cease-fire is the 
resignation of the president and the formation of a summit 
between the leaders of jehadi and political groups. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

