<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Cited on GATT Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601133994 Tehran IRNA in English 1251 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 6, IRNA -- Membership in General 
Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) can play a determining 
role in development and expansion of world economy, said a 
Foreign Ministry official here Wednesday [5 January]. 
  Head of the international organizations department of 
Foreign 
Ministry, Bozorgmehr Ziaran, in an interview with the English 
daily `TEHRAN TIMES' published today commented on Iran's 
decision to apply for membership in GATT. 
  "Formation of such a large multilateral trade organization 
after seven years of exhaustive discussions would strengthen the 
previous international ties between member states in such fields 
as agriculture, industry and textile," Ziaran added. 
  On membership of the Islamic Republic of Iran in GATT, he 
said "It is a matter of utmost importance for our country's 
decision-makers to consider the articles of this world agreement 
deeply and meticulously before making the proper final choice. 
Such an important decision should be made in a way that will 
minimize the risk of any damage to our national economy," the 
Foreign Ministry official stressed. 
  As for official stand on the issue, he said "Serious 
discussions have been going on for quite some time now, but the 
policy makers of the Islamic Republic have not yet announced 
their decision." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

