<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkmenistan President, Delegation End Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Niyazov Granted Honorary Citizenship </H4>
<F P=102> LD0601124394 Tehran IRNA in English 1151 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 6, IRNA -- On the final day of his 
five-day state visit to Iran, Turkmen President Saparmurad 
Niyazov was granted an honorary citizenship status by Tehran 
Mayor Gholam Hoseyn Karbaschi, Thursday [6 January]. 
  Speaking at the ceremony, also attended by Iranian President 
Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani, Niyazov lauded Tehran's municipality 
for granting him honorary citizenship, saying this indicated the 
durability and continuation of reciprocal services between the 
two nations. 
  He said the frontiers separating the two countries in the 
past have now been turned into border of friendship. 
  The Turkmen president saying he was certain of fruitfulness 
of his visit to Iran, noted relations between the two 
neighboring governments not only benefit the two states but also 
play a key role in world political scene. 
  President Hashemi-Rafsanjani said that plan on mutual 
cooperation formulated between the two countries during 
President Niyazov's stay in Iran was a step towards bringing 
mutual relations closer. 
  The Iranian president said that he and his Turkmen 
counterpart will support any measure aimed at broadening 
Tehran-Ashgabat relations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

