<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkmenistan President, Delegation End Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Cooperation Agreements Signed </H4>
<F P=102> LD0601134294 Tehran IRNA in English 1212 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 6, (IRNA) -- Iran and Turkmenistan on 
Thursday [6 January] signed several letters of understanding for 
political, military and border cooperation. 
  The documents were signed by the visiting Turkmen President 
Saparmurad Niyazov before his departure at the end of a five-day 
state visit and his Iranian counterpart President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  Meanwhile, several other letters of understanding were inked 
between the Turkmen officials and their Iranian counterparts 
including one on joint cooperation to combat drug trafficking by 
Iranian and Turkmen nationals. The document was signed by 
Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati and his Turkmen counterpart. 
  Minister of Roads and Transportation Akbar Torkan signed a 
letter of understanding on bilateral cooperation on railways and 
shipping with his Turkmen counterpart. 
  An economic-trade letter of understanding was signed by 
Iran's Commerce Minister Yahya ol-Eshaq and his Turkmen 
counterpart. 
  Another letter was inked on bilateral cooperation in the 
field of oil by Oil Minister Gholam Reza Aqazadeh-Kho'i and his 
Turkmen counterpart. 
  A letter was signed by Iran's head of customs department 
Abdul Hoseyn Vahaji and his Turkmen counterpart on transit of 
goods and costums affairs. 
  Minister of Energy Bijan Namdar-Zanganeh signed a letter of 
understanding with his Turkmen counterpaert on energy and 
transfer of surplus Turkmen electricity to other countries 
through the Iranian territory. 
  Governors general of central banks of Iran and Turkmenistan 
signed a letter of understanding for improving Tehran-Ashgabat 
banking relations. 

</TEXT>

