<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkmenistan President, Delegation End Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   President Bids Farewell to Niyazov </H4>
<F P=102> LD0601135494 Tehran IRNA in English 1232 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 6, (IRNA) -- Seeing off Turkmen 
President Saparmurad Niyazov at the end of his five-day official 
visit to Iran Thursday [6 January], President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani termed Niyazov's visit to Tehran as a 
"turning point" in mutual relations. 
  The two presidents also announced that promotion of 
Tehran-Ashgabat relations will gain further momentum from now on. 
  The Turkmen president told reporters at Tehran's Mehrabad 
International Airport that three historical documents had been 
inked between the two countries during his visit. 
  "The Turkmen delegation did a great job in conjunction with 
their Iranian counterparts in economic, trade and cultural 
fields...the agreements reached between the two countries will 
entail great results for both nations in the future," he said. 
  Hojatoleslam Hashemi-Rafsanjani said that the visit of 
President Niyazov to Tehran is unique compared with other 
official visits made to Iran, because all Turkmen cabinet 
ministers, Friday prayer leaders and other influential officials 
of that country were present here. 
  Hashemi-Rafsanjani maintained that mutual cooperation will 
take a greater momentum after President Niyazov's visit, adding 
that this would be beneficiary to other countries of the region. 

</TEXT>

