Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Following the opening of Brunei's embassy in 
Tehran, (Haj Suhini Bin Haj Muhammad Hassan), that country's 
first charge d'affaires in the Islamic Republic of Iran, 
yesterday met with the Iranian foreign minister, Mr. Velayati 
and presented his credentials. 
  In the meeting, the two officials discussed the expansion 
and 
the strengthening of the two countries' relations, and the 
coming visit of the sultan of Brunei, Haj Hassan Bolkiah, to 
Iran. 
  The Bruneian charge d'affaires considered the Islamic 
Republic of Iran as a second home, and stressed the willingness 
of his country's officials in strengthening relations with the 
Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Pointing to the results of their previous meetings and 
discussions of the two countries' officials, and the positive 
steps which have been taken in line with the two countries' 
ties, Mr. Velayati considered the Bruneian ruler's coming visit 
to Iran as a significant step for expansion of relations. 
