<H3> <TI>   Campaign To Expel `Afghan' Arabs To Begin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0601172494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 6 Jan 94 p1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0601172494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "A Pakistani Campaign Soon for the </F>
Deportation of `Afghan' Arabs"] 
  [Text] Islamabad, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Official 
Pakistani sources yesterday confirmed that hundreds of "Afghan" 
Arabs living in Afghanistan [as published] are now targets for 
detention and deportation to their countries of origin within 
the next few weeks. A foreign ministry spokesman in Islamabad 
has stated that Algeria, Egypt, and Tunisia had officially 
requested that Pakistan expel their extremist nationals residing 
in Pakistan. 
  The spokesman added that "solving this problem is also 
important for Pakistan." 
  Pakistan is expected to begin its campaign in the next few 
weeks to avoid the possibility of its name being added to the 
U.S. list of "states which sponsor terrorism." It is known that 
the U.S. State Department is now reviewing that list prior to 
issuing a new list in February. 

</TEXT>

