<F P=102>  BK0701091894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0701091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The scheduled third trial of the medium-range 
surface-to-surface missile, Agni, has been postponed. The 
test-firing of the country's most sophisticated missile was to 
be carried out today at the interim test range at Chandipur in 
Orissa. Our correspondent, quoting official sources in 
Balasore, reports that the trial was postponed at the last stage 
of the countdown this morning because of some technical snag. 
The exact date of the launching will be notified later. 

</TEXT>

