<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Singh Meets With UAE Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0601160694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0601160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India and the United Arab Emirates [UAE] have agreed 
to sign an extradition treaty to help contain terrorism. This 
was decided at a meeting in New Delhi today between the UAE 
foreign minister, Mr. Mohammad Khalifa Bin Yusuf al-Zubaidi, and 
the external affairs minister, Mr. Dinesh Singh. An External 
Affairs Ministry release later said that considerable headway 
has been made in this regard. Discussions at the levels of 
experts will be held in Abu Dhabi at an early date. The two 
countries also signed an agreement to control narcotics and drug 
trafficking by exchanging information and increasing 
cooperation. At the end of the three days of the joint 
commission meeting, the two countries also signed a cultural 
exchange program for 1994-96. At their meeting, both Mr. 
al-Zubaidi and Mr. Dinesh Singh expressed satisfaction at the 
recommencement of India-Pakistan dialogue. The two ministers 
hoped that the process will continue. 

</TEXT>

