<F P=102>  EA0601182094 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1015 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0601182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo 6 Jan (SUNA) -- Brigadier al-Tijani Khalifah, 
director of air operations at the Civil Aviation Authority, is 
currently on a visit to Cairo. Yesterday he stated that the 
Russian Antonov aircraft, which is on hire to certain quarters 
in Sudan, and whose Russian crew fled with it last week and 
landed at Luxor Airport, had been carrying foodstuffs belonging 
to the World Food Program from al-Ubayyid to Bahr al-Ghazal. In 
a news conference he held in Cairo, he said that the aircraft 
arrived in Sudan in accordance with a commercial contract with a 
Sudanese commercial aviation company, and that the Sudanese 
Government was not a party to the contract. 
  Brig. al-Tijani Khalifah denied the claims of the aircraft 
crew, published by the Egyptian press, that Sudanese authorities 
had been holding the aircraft. He said: We in Sudan did not 
imprison any crew in Sudan. He pointed out that there were six 
sets of foreign crews for air transport in the country. 

</TEXT>

