<F P=103> LD0701114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Doha, 7 Jan -- Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad al-Jabir 
al-Sabah, first deputy prime minister and minister of foreign 
affairs, has revealed in press statements published here that he 
will visit Yemen, but did not mention the date of the visit. 
  In statements to the Qatari press reported by the QATARI 
NEWS 
AGENCY [QNA], Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad said that the program of his 
foreign tour included a visit to Yemen, but the current 
conditions that Yemen was experiencing did not allow this visit. 
  He added "when these conditions end and disappear I will 
visit Sanaa." 
  The first deputy prime minister and minister of foreign 
affairs expressed regrets over current events in Yemen. He also 
expressed regrets and astonishment for the rumors implicating 
Kuwait in the rift and dispute between north and south Yemen, 
saying that this is void of truth and a mere fabrication. 
  He pointed out that Kuwait is very far removed from the 
dispute that the state of Yemen is currently experiencing and 
this matter "hurts us very much." [passage omitted] 

