<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Afghan, Iraqi Refugees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601172694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] In an interview with our 
reporter on the return of the Afghan refugees or their 
settlement in Iran, Interior Minister Mr. Besharati-Jahromi 
said: At present some 700,000 Afghan refugees live in our 
country. On the basis of a project prepared by the UNHCR a 
number of Afghan immigrants voluntarily returned home, before 
the recent civil war and fratricide in Afghanistan. As of next 
Nowruz [21 March 1994], the said project will be followed up; 
however, if there are some who desire to stay in Iran, then we 
will issue cards for them. [passage omitted] 
  The interior minister said Iraqi refugees in Iran numbered 
around 50,000. 

</TEXT>

