<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   BJP Leader Objects to Clinton Letter on Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0701125094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0701125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] says India should 
formally register a protest with the United States against its 
attitude toward Kashmir. Addressing a news conference in New 
Delhi today, the party president, Mr. L.K. Advani, took 
exception to a letter reportedly written by President Clinton to 
a Washington-based supporter of militancy in Kashmir. Replying 
to questions, Mr. Advani said that Pakistan should be told that 
any further talks on Kashmir will depend on Islamabad ending its 
proxy war and the inclusion of the future of Pakistan-occupied 
Kashmir in the agenda. 

</TEXT>

