<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th, Shahaq Hold Private Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001113694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1045 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1001113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Taba, 10 Jan (MENA)--Heads of the Palestinian and 
Israeli delegations to the Taba talks, Palestinian president's 
adviser Nabil Sha'th and Israeli Deputy Chief of Staff Amnon 
Shahaq, held a private meeting in Taba immediately after the 
Israeli delegation arrived at the hotel today. 
  MENA learned that they discussed a plan for the negotiations 
in this round, which is scheduled to continue until Thursday or 
Friday morning and then resume in the next two weeks to reach an 
agreement on implementing Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and 
Jericho. 
  Members of the two delegations joined the meeting later. 
During the afternoon session, the delegations are due to form 
subcommittees to discuss the disputed issues, basically, the 
border crossings, the size of Jericho, and the security of the 
Israeli settlements. Sea, air, and road security and how to 
control it in accordance with the Palestinian-Israeli 
Declaration of Principles signed in Washington on 13 September 
will also be discussed. 
  The Civil Committee concerned with the transfer of the 
self-rule power, which formerly met in al-'Arish, is scheduled 
to open meetings in Taba on Tuesday morning. 

</TEXT>

