<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Damascus Declaration Meeting Opens 9 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Agenda Detailed </H4>
<F P=102> JN0901170594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0901170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The meeting of the foreign ministers of the Arab 
countries that signed the Damascus Declaration opened in 
Damascus this evening. During the meeting, which will continue 
until tomorrow, the ministers will focus on evaluating the march 
of the Damascus Declaration and the difficulties facing it. 
They will also examine practical steps to activate the 
principles of the declaration and implement its provisions in 
order to reinforce cooperation among the Damascus Declaration 
countries in various fields. Moreover, the ministers will 
discuss the international and regional situation, especially 
developments in the peace process in light of the anticipated 
summit between President Hafiz al-Asad and U.S. President Bill 
Clinton. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

