<H4>   Musa, Saudi Minister Meet on `Sidelines' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0901142094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1355 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0901142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 9 Jan (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
held consultations in Damascus this afternoon on the sidelines 
of the Damascus Declaration foreign ministers' conference. 
  Musa met with Saudi Minister of Foreign Affairs Sa'ud 
al-Faysal and discussed ways to develop the Damascus Declaration 
in light of the conditions and challenges facing the Arab 
nation. They also discussed the Arab and international 
situations and the developments in the peace negotiations. 
  Musa is scheduled to meet with Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar' before the conference of the Damascus Declaration 
foreign ministers begins at 1800 today. 

</TEXT>

