<H3> <TI>   Discusses Cooperation With Mubarak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001111294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1020 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1001111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 10 Jan (MENA)--President Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak received U.S. Senator Richard Shelby and the delegation 
accompanying him this morning. U.S. Charge d'Affaires in Cairo 
Edmund Hall attended. 
  The U.S. senator said afterward that he and President 
Mubarak 
reviewed Egypt's positive role in the Middle East. He said he 
informed President Mubarak that he realizes the importance of 
relations with Egypt for stability throughout the region. 
  Shelby said they discussed bilateral ties and various 
aspects 
of U.S.-Egyptian cooperation. 
  The meeting also dealt with expanding bilateral relations in 
the economic and military areas. 

</TEXT>

