<H3> <TI>   Jordanian Ambassador Meets Musa, Views PLO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0801121894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1000 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0801121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Jan (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa met 
today with Jordanian Ambassador in Cairo Nayif Sa'ud al-Qadi. 
Al-Qadi said after the meeting that he briefed Musa on the 
results of the Palestinian delegation's talks with Jordanian 
officials in Amman. 
  Referring to the signing of an economic accord between 
Jordan 
and the PLO, he affirmed his country's eagerness for solid 
relations with the PLO, for an agreement to be reached on all 
topics, and for the two sides to have a common vision for the 
future. He noted that relations should be normal because this 
will serve both the Jordanian and Palestinian sides. 
  The ambassador said that he and Musa discussed ways to boost 
bilateral relations and to prepare for convening the Joint 
Higher Committee soon under the chairmanship of the two 
countries' prime ministers. 

</TEXT>

