<F P=102>  NC0901072594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0901072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Husni Mubarak has announced that the 
dialogue with all national forces that he asked for is likely to 
begin in the second half of February. The president said: The 
situation in Egypt is much better when compared to other 
countries, especially as we implement economic reforms that we 
consider to be in the best interests of most of our citizens. 
  In an exclusive interview with MAYU, he said that the state 
is eager to protect national industry in every way. He urged 
Egypt's youth not to be misled by calls of perversion, no matter 
what the temptation. He also urged the Arab brothers to close 
the files of the past and look to the future in a spirit of 
optimism, solidarity, and cooperation. 

