<F P=103> NC0801170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 8 Jan (MENA) -- The Supreme State Security 
Court-Emergency decided at its session today to postpone the 
trial of the 48 defendants, led by Dr. 'Umar 'Abd-al-Rahman, who 
are accused of taking part in riots in al-Fayyum in 1989; it is 
postponed until Monday, 10 January, in order to listen to the 
defense presentation. 
  The indictment was read at the beginning of the court 
session. It accused the defendants of taking part in 
demonstrations following Friday prayers in al-Shuhada' Mosque in 
al-Fayyum in 1989, of carrying firearms and ammunition without a 
license, using them in activities that undermine public law and 
order, attacking members of the authorities, and attempted 
murder. 
  Usamah Qandil, president of the Supreme State Security 
Prosecution, stated that escaped defendant Muhsin Muhammad Ahmad 
Kharallah, who is involved in this case, had been arrested on 
court order. The defendant attended today's session. [passage 
