Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] During his visit to Malakal, Muhammad al-Amin 
Khalifah, the speaker of the Transitional National Assembly 
[TNA], met with a group of leaders from the united faction of 
the rebel movement, from the area of Fanjak. They came there to 
hold negotiations with state authorities, with the objective of 
taking part in development and construction. Mr. Khalifah 
commended the decision of the group to join the national march 
and take part in reconstruction in the Upper Nile State. 
  He said that their return had come at the same time as the 
country's celebrations marking its independence. 
  Colonel Thomas Dod, the leader of the group, which also 
included 11 other officers, said that his forces had decided to 
return and surrender their weapons, as they wanted to take part 
in reconstruction. He said that his group was in need of 
essential services such as education, health, and agricultural 
inputs for the people of the area. [passage omitted] 

