<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres: No Target Date for Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1001131694 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1230 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1001131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israel will not withdraw from Gaza and Jericho on 
14 April, the date set in the Declaration of Principles [DOP] 
with the PLO. This may be inferred from the remarks of Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres, who said today that there is no target 
date for the withdrawal. Rather, he said, there is an 
understanding that the implementation of the DOP will last four 
months after the agreement has been signed. Peres was asked 
whether that meant that the withdrawal would start toward the 
beginning of summer, and he replied: We will try to do it 
earlier. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1300 GMT on 10 January 
quotes Peres as "voicing his confidence that progress will be 
made in the Taba talks and noting that the DOP cannot be 
implemented in one go."] 

</TEXT>

