<H3> <TI>   MK Claims Documents Prove IDF Pullout Date </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0801121994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 8 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0801121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tzomet Knesset Member [MK] Eli'ezer Zandberg said he 
has documents from the Defense Ministry and the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] stating that the evacuation of Army forces from 
the Gaza Strip will begin on 22 February and take two days. 
Zandberg asserted that it is now clear that all the 
disagreements between Israel and the PLO were but a show that 
was intended to conceal information from the public. 
  In reaction, Meretz Knesset faction chairman Ran Kohen said 
that the documents disclosed by Zandberg were bogus. Kohen told 
our correspondent Hayim Hecht that he had checked with the IDF 
and the Defense Ministry and was informed that no date had been 
set for the start of the withdrawal from the Gaza Strip, since 
the timetable for the evacuation process depended on the results 
of the negotiations with the Palestinians. This week a Knesset 
plenum will discuss a motion on the agenda presented by MK 
Zandberg on the issue of the withdrawal from the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

