<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beilin on al-Asad, Agreement on West Bank </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0801183094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 8 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0801183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin said today that 
he expects President al-Asad to tell President Clinton that he 
intends to establish full peace with Israel. If Syria is 
willing to establish full diplomatic relations and open borders, 
Israel is willing to withdraw on the Golan -- not from the Golan 
-- following the formula that the depth of withdrawal equals the 
depth of peace. 
  Speaking to our correspondent, Deputy Minister Beilin said 
that an agreement has been reached with the Palestinians that 
the entire West Bank will be demilitarized with no Palestinian 
army or guns, and that Israel will militarily supervise the 
entire West Bank. At the same time, whether an Israeli military 
presence at every location in the West Bank is necessary still 
needs to be discussed. 

</TEXT>

