  In Israel, there are rising expectations for a positive 
shift 
in the negotiations with Syria following the Clinton-al-Asad 
summit. A senior political source, however, told our 
correspondent that the prime minister will have to slow down the 
pace of negotiations on the Golan Heights because, at this 
stage, he will be unable to deal simultaneously with 
negotiations with Syria and the Palestinians. 

