<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Update on Incidents in Territories 10 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1001175894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1001175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A terrorist attack was foiled today in the local 
police station in Ramallah. A young Arab woman from Kafr 'Aqab 
in the Ramallah District entered the station, pulled out a gun, 
and aimed it at a policeman. When a security officer pointed 
his gun at her, she let go of her weapon. She was detained for 
interrogation by the Judaea District police. 
  A booby-trapped car was identified and safely defused today 
in Jerusalem's French Hill. 
  An aide of the leader of the military wing of Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] in Judaea and Samaria was today sentenced 
by the Nabulus military court to seven years in prison. He had 
planned to detonate a car bomb in East Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

