<F P=102>  NC1001150194 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 1430 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1001150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] A U.S. Congressional delegation today made a 
tour of al-Biqa' as part of its quest for information on Israeli 
soldiers imprisoned or missing in Lebanon. The team met with a 
number of Lebanese and Syrian officers in al-Biqa'. During the 
tour, the team was accompanied by six military vehicles carrying 
special units from the Lebanese Army as well as an armored 
vehicle that belongs to a U.S. security team. 
  Shaykh Nabil Qawuq, Hizballah Consultative Council member, 
held a news conference in Sidon in which he called for the 
release of all Lebanese and Palestinian prisoners held in Israel 
in exchange for releasing two [as heard] Israeli soldiers 
captured by Hizballah. Shaykh Qawuq denied that Israeli pilot 
Ron Arad is being held by Hizballah, adding that knowing his 
fate is a matter that concerns Israel. He also denied any 
direct contacts between Hizballah and the U.S. Congress. He 
noted that the United States is a full partner with Israel and 
therefore cannot act as a mediator. [passage omitted] 
  According to the latest reports, the U.S. team concluded its 
visit to al-Biqa' at 1500 today and left for Syria. The team is 
supposed to hold a news conference in Damascus to announce the 
results of its visit to Lebanon. 

