<H3> <TI>   Committee Denounces Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001062494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0530 GMT 10 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1001062494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The follow-up committee in support of Lebanese 
detainees in the Zionist enemy's prisons has denounced the visit 
of a U.S. Congressional delegation to discuss the fate of 
missing Israeli soldiers while it ignores the fate of hundreds 
of Lebanese detainees in al-Khiyam prison [in Israel's security 
zone in south Lebanon] and the occupied territories' [Israeli] 
prisons. 
  In a statement issued today, the follow-up committee said 
the 
humanity of the U.S. Congressional delegation is confined to 
Israeli soldiers while the fate of 300 prisoners in Israeli 
prisons is ignored. For over nine years Israel has refused to 
allow the International Committee of the Red Cross to visit 
al-Khiyam prison. And over 165 Lebanese have been held in the 
enemy's prisons since the 1982 invasion. Israel is also holding 
the bodies of 125 martyrs. 
  The committee said this shows the inhumane nature of the 
U.S. 
stance, which uses Israeli double standards and views our issue 
with an Israeli eye. 
  The committee called on the Lebanese Government to adopt a 
firm stance on the international silence regarding the issue of 
the detainees. 

</TEXT>

