<H3> <TI>   Fadlallah Backs Iran Against `World Arrogance' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701223194 Tehran IRNA in English 1625 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0701223194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, Jan 7, IRNA -- Leading Lebanese Muslim 
leader al-'Allamah Seyyed Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah said in his 
Friday prayer sermons here today that the world Muslims should 
be on the side of Islamic Iran in its encounter with the attacks 
of world arrogance. 
  He said the word `fundamentalism' is a result of the western 
propaganda and has been used with the idea of discrediting the 
political opposition to the west. 
  Fadlallah said Arab governments should learn a lesson from 
what has befallen the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) 
and learn also that their recognition of the Zionist regime will 
offer them only infamy and wretchedness. 
  Meanwhile in the northern Lebanese city of Tripoli, leader 
of 
the Islamic Unity Movement of Lebanon, Sheykh sa'id Sha'ban, 
said during his Friday prayer sermons today that the United 
States and other arrogant world governments are drafting a 
scheme with which to pit Muslim and Arab nations against one 
another. 
  He criticized the Arab governments that promote the goals of 
the United States. 
  Sha'ban said had the resources of Muslim governments been 
devoted to the promotion of the Islamic movement the world would 
now have witnessed the creation of a big Islamic force. 

</TEXT>

