<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Dead in Continuing Kashmir Protest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1001145094 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1001145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reports from occupied Kashmir speak of widespread 
demonstrations and strikes against the Indian military siege of 
Dargah Hazratbal [shrine] to prevent the devotees from ziyarat 
[paying respect to] of mue-i-mubarak [holy hair] on the occasion 
of Merajunnabi [anniversary of prophet Mohammad's ascension to 
heaven]. 
  The demonstrations were particularly violent in Srinagar, 
Baramula, Kupwara, Anantnag-Islamabad, Sopor, Badgam, and 
Pulwama. The demonstrators raised slogans and demanded complete 
withdrawal of Indian troops from around the dargah. Meanwhile, 
repressive siege and search operations by the occupation forces 
continue unabated all across the valley. The mojahedin in 
retaliation attacked the Indian troops and killed three of them. 
Three mojahedin were martyred in a clash near Badgam. Three 
bullet-riddled bodies suspected to be killed by the Indian 
troops have been recovered in Kupwara. 

</TEXT>

