Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 8, IRNA -- Russia's Special Envoy for 
Karabakh Affairs, Vladimir Kazimirov, here today met with a 
senior Iranian to discuss current regional condition and the 
ways and means to end Karabakh crisis. 
  Kazimirov, who arrived here Thursday [6 January], briefed 
Director General of Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) and 
the Caucasus Affairs Department at the Foreign Ministry, Morteza 
Bank, on the measures taken by his country to end Karabakh 
crisis. 
  He underscored the role the regional countries and Minsk 
Group as well as the European Cooperation and Security 
Conference can play in ending the Karabakh issue. 
  Bank said in return that Islamic Republic of Iran is ready 
to 
intensify its efforts to put an end to war in Karabakh enclave. 

