<F P=102>  LD0801172694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mr. John William Kachamila, Mozambique's minister of 
mineral resources, who is carrying a message by his country's 
president for President Hashemi-Rafsanjani, today met with First 
Vice President Hasan Habibi and called for the expansion of 
economic, industrial, political, and cultural relations with the 
Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  In turn, Habibi expressed satisfaction over the success of 
the struggle of African nations against racism and said: The 
just struggle of the African people, particularly in the south, 
against racism has always been supported by Iran and now that 
there is a gradual solution to this internationally shameful 
problem in South Africa, we support the process of stability and 
peace in the region. 
  The first vice president said the presence of the African 
nation of Mozambique in the Islamic Conference Organization was 
useful in creating better understanding between African and 
Islamic nations, and stressed the need for an exchange of views 
and experiences between the officials of the two countries aimed 
at expanding relations in various fields. 

