<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Prime Minister Silajdzic Arrives 9 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0901103294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0600 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0901103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic 
arrived in Islamabad this morning on a three-day visit to 
Pakistan. Talking to newsmen at the airport, Silajdzic 
criticized the international community for failing to play an 
effective role in ending the Serb and Croat aggression against 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. He urged the international community to 
either act effectively to defend the Bosnian Muslims or allow 
them to defend themselves. He also called for an end to the 
arms embargo against Bosnia, which he described as illegal. He 
said the arms embargo against his country has caused the 
massacre of 200,000 Muslims. Silajdzic said renewed shelling 
and bombing by the Serb and Croat forces of Sarajevo and other 
cities has seriously hurt the process of restoring peace in 
Bosnia. He said Bosnia-Herzegovina is trying to restore peace, 
but the siege of Sarajevo is hampering this process. 
  Silajdzic praised Pakistan's role in the Bosnian crisis and 
its continued support for the Muslim people of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  During his stay in Pakistan, Silajdzic will call on 
President 
Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari and meet with Prime Minister Benazir 
Bhutto. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

