<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK's Archer Addresses Kurdistan Parliament </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601173194 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601173194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lord Jeffrey Archer, envoy of British Prime Minister 
John Major, delivered a speech at a meeting held by the 
Kurdistan parliament yesterday. The meeting was attended by 
Parliamentary Speaker Jawhar Namiq Salim; Deputy Speaker Najat 
Ahmad 'Aziz Zadah; Kurdistan Prime Minister Kusret Rasul; 
Muhammad Tawfiq Rahim, minister of humanitarian affairs and 
cooperation; and Khurshar Zibari, member of the Political Bureau 
of the Unified Kurdistan Democratic Party. 
  The session was opened by the parliamentary speaker, who 
delivered a speech in which he welcomed Mr. Archer and spoke 
about his role in supporting the cause of the Kurdish people. 
He also noted the long relationship between the Kurdish people 
and Mr. Archer and his important role in supporting our people. 
The parliamentary speaker also praised the British Government's 
positive role in supporting democracy and human rights in the 
world in general, and in Iraq in particular, and its role in the 
implementation of UN Security Council Resolution 688. 
  Mr. Archer then delivered a speech which he began by reading 
a letter that British Prime Minister John Major addressed to the 
parliament and the regional government in Kurdistan. 

</TEXT>

