<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurdistan Islamic Movement Branch Joins KDP </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0701120194 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1535 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0701120194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text of statement issued by the Fifth Branch of the </F>
Islamic Movement of Iraqi Kurdistan on joining the Kurdistan 
Democratic Party" on 31 December 1993; place not given--read by 
announcer] 
  [Text] Recent events in the Kurdish arena, represented by 
the regrettable internecine fighting, have had negative effects 
and repercussions on the Kurdistan liberation movement. We 
acknowledge the domestic and foreign negative effects of these 
events. We appreciate the noble stands of the leader of the 
Kurdish people, Mas'ud Barzani, leader of the Kurdistan 
Democratic Party [KDP], to prevent an armed clash and later to 
stop and contain it in order to avoid bloodshed. This stand 
indicates his concern for the wellbeing of his people and his 
devotion and sincerity. Appreciating these noble stands by the 
KDP and its leader, Barzani, and following the approval of the 
guide of the Islamic Movement, Shaykh (?'Ali) al-'Uthman in 
accordance with his cable dated 30 December 1993, we declare 
that the Fifth Branch of the Islamic Movement, the (Badinan) 
region, will join the KDP. On this occasion, we extend our 
thanks and appreciation for all the good efforts that have been 
exerted and prevented the occurrence of problems and an armed 
clash in the (Badinan) area. We thank God Almighty that He 
enabled us to control the situation throughout the past period 
during which Kurdistan, with the exception of the (Badinan) 
region, witnessed such regrettable incidents. We thank God and 
the good sons of our proud Kurdish people. 
  [Signed] The Fifth Branch of the Islamic Movement of 
Kurdistan 
  [Dated] 31 December 1993 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

