<H3> <TI>   Minister Departs for Saudi Arabia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0801150994 Muscat Radio Oman Network in Arabic 1300 GMT 8 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0801150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Muscat Radio Oman Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Yusuf Bin-'Alawi Bin-'Abdallah, minister of state 
for foreign affairs, left the country today for Riyadh on a 
short visit to fraternal Saudi Arabia. This visit will be 
followed by a visit to the fraternal Hashemite Kingdom of 
Jordan. His excellency will also go to Damascus tomorrow to 
take part in the meetings of the foreign ministers of the 
Damascus Declaration, which is comprised of the Gulf Cooperation 
Council member states, Egypt, and Syria. On Tuesday, his 
excellency will go to Cairo to hold talks with a number of 
Egyptian officials. On Wednesday, he will visit fraternal Yemen 
and hold talks with the Yemeni officials. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

