<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Qatar </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amir Receives Kuwaiti Foreign Minister, Letter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0801114094 Manama WAKH in Arabic 1025 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0801114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Doha, 8 Jan (WAKH)--His Highness Shaykh Khalifah 
Bin-Hamad Al Thani, amir of Qatar, has received a letter from 
His Highness Shaykh Jabir al-Ahmad al-Sabah, amir of Kuwait, 
dealing with developments in the region, the march of the Gulf 
Cooperation Council [GCC], and bilateral relations. The letter 
also thanks Qatar for its position in support of Kuwait. 
  Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad, Kuwaiti first deputy prime minister 
and foreign minister, delivered the letter when his highness the 
amir of Qatar received him here today. During the meeting, they 
discussed regional, Arab, and international developments and 
ways to enhance bilateral relations in various fields. 
  Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad's visit to Qatar is part of a tour of 
the GCC states during which he will deliver similar letters to 
their leaders. 

</TEXT>

