<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Balladur, Delegation Pay Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Juppe Meets Foreign Minister </H4>
<F P=102> LD0801203394 Riyadh SPA in English 1947 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0801203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, Jan 8, SPA -- Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal, the 
foreign minister held a meeting here tonight with his French 
counterpart, Alain Juppe who is accompanying Prime Minister 
Edouard Balladur in his current visit to the Kingdom. 
  During the meeting, matters of mutual interest including 
situation of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the peace process in the 
Middle East were discussed. 
  The meeting was attended by 'Abd-al-Rahman Mansuri, 
undersecretary of the Foreign Ministry for political affairs, 
Jamil al-Hujaylan, the Saudi ambassador to France and a number 
of senior officials of the Foreign Ministry. 
  From the French side, the meeting was attended by Dennis 
Bochard director of the Middle East Department at the French 
Foreign Ministry Emi Bertard, advisor at the Office of the 
Foreign Minister and John Pierre deputy head of the Middle East 
Department. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
